      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=### Input Data\n[\n  {\n  \"title\": \"{{ $('Loop').item.json.title }}\",\n  \"company\": \"{{ $('Loop').item.json.company }}\",\n  \"company_url\": \"{{ $('Loop').item.json.company_url }}\",\n  \"results\": {{ JSON.stringify($json.results) }}\n  }\n]\n",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "=---\n\n**Task**\nFrom the provided **`results` array**, select **exactly one** URL where a **job-application email address is most likely to be found**, based on page purpose and structure — **even if no email address is visible in the search snippet**.\n\n**Important Assumption**\n\n* You **will NOT see the email address directly** in the search result snippets.\n* You must **infer** the most probable URL where a valid job-application email would exist if the page were opened.\n\n**Selection Priority (highest to lowest)**\n\n1. Company careers or jobs pages (e.g., `/careers`, `/jobs`, `/work-with-us`)\n2. Company legal, imprint, or contact pages (e.g., `/imprint`, `/impressum`, `/legal`, `/contact`)\n3. Company homepage\n4. Other URLs **only if** they are plausibly relevant for finding a job-application email\n\n**Hard Constraints**\n\n* You **must choose only from URLs present in the `results` array**.\n* Select **one URL only**.\n* **EXCLUDE** any URLs from the following domains (including subdomains/international versions):\n* stepstone.de\n* linkedin.com\n* xing.com\n* glassdoor.de\n* jooble.org\n* stellenanzeigen.de\n* remotely.de\n* itsteps.de\n* jobs.heise.de\n* smarterinterim.de\n* jobs.noz.de\n* jobs.stellencockpit.de\n\n\n* If **no URL reasonably qualifies**, return `null`.\n\n**Output Format (strict)**\nReturn **only** the following JSON array.\nNo explanations, no markdown, no additional text.\n\n```\n[{\"url\":\"string|null\"}]\n\n```\n\n---\n"
            }
          ]
        },
